CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, reads;" Wendell Willkie, Republican candidate for President, stopped off in Pittsburgh's famous Hill District last Thursday when he made a 50-mile tour of the city and its environs before his main speech and bid for the labor vote at Forbes Field in evening. The candidate's Hill District stop and speech were made in front of The Pittsburgh Courier plant at Centre Avenue and Francis street.  Willkie greeting throngs on Wylie avenue."
TitMainTitle: Wendell Willkie standing in back of open convertible, for campaign stop, Hill District
